e 50 and over, dealing with such subjects as retirement planning, health and legislation affecting the elderly. An added staff member will be assigned to this package, called `` Prime Time.'' In his `` report card'' to the members, <PERSON> Boccardi </PERSON> also said the AP this year will complete the conversion to a 9,000-word-a-minute high-speed transmission system for <ORGANIZATION> DataStream </ORGANIZATION> and DataFeature news copy, after a delay caused by a worldwide shortage of advanced computer memory chips. He also said a new highspeed photo service, PhotoStream, will be running on a test-basis by mid-year. The <ORGANIZATION> AP </ORGANIZATION>'s annual report noted that 72 more daily newspapers joined the news cooperative in 1988, bringing total membership at the end of 1988 to 1,483 dailies, representing 95 percent of daily <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> newspaper circulation. The meeting agenda also included election of seven members of the <ORGANIZATION> AP </ORGANIZATION>'s 21-member board of directors, including three new members. All members were elected to three-year terms. The new board members are: <PERSON> William </PERSON> <PERSON> M. </PERSON> <PERSON> Boyd </PERSON> <PERSON> Jr. </PERSON> of the <ORGANIZATION> Central </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Jersey </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Home </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> News </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Brunswick </ORGANIZATION>; <PERSON> William </PERSON> <PERSON> R. </PERSON> <PERSON> Burleigh </PERSON>, senior vice president-newspapers and publishing, <ORGANIZATION> Scripps </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Howard </ORGANIZATION>; and <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> G. </PERSON> <PERSON> Montgomery </PERSON> of <ORGANIZATION> The </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Daily </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Union </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Junction </ORGANIZATI