<HEAD>Car Smashes Through House, Misses Sleeping Couple</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KINGSTON, Mass. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A sports car crashed into a house and tore through a bedroom but missed the couple sleeping there. The car left the street at about 1:30 a.m. Sunday, ran up a small embankment and hurtled through the air. It glanced off a pickup truck parked outside the house, crashed through the house and landed about 35 feet away in a yard next door. `` All I heard was a big explosion and glass smashing and the wall came in and fell on me,'' said <PERSON> Ronald </PERSON> <PERSON> Viator </PERSON>, the owner of the house. `` If they had n't hit my pickup, they would have come through the wall and landed on top of my wife and me.'' The driver of the car was taken to <LOCATION> Jordan </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Hospital </LOCATION> in <LOCATION> Plymouth </LOCATION> with cuts and bruises and released. A passenger suffered a broken breastbone. <PERSON> Viator </PERSON> and his wife, <PERSON> Ann </PERSON>, escaped serious injury. Their children, 9-year-old <PERSON> Jennifer </PERSON> and 5-year-old <PERSON> Jessica </PERSON>, were asleep in their bedroom in a far corner of the house and were not injured.
