 day of the year. It is the home of the world's only Sisserou parrots and the only full-blooded Carib Indians, and the waters off its southwestern coast are considered a scuba diver's paradise. <PERSON> Benjamin </PERSON> also praises his country's 95 percent literacy rate, a new highway network, the doubling of <LOCATION> Dominica </LOCATION>'s production of bananas _ its main export _ an excellent debt-payment record and plans to build an international airport to spur tourist traffic. The ambassador reminds people that he represents the Commonwealth of <LOCATION> Dominica </LOCATION>, not the <LOCATION> Dominican </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Republic </LOCATION>, even though his embassy receives phone calls and mail _ some of it top secret _ for the other, much larger <LOCATION> Caribbean </LOCATION> nation. Says Benjamin: `` Whenever I see the ambassador from the <LOCATION> Dominican </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Republic </LOCATION>, I say, ` Would n't it be a good idea for us to merge our two embassies? Then we could share our secrets fully'.''
