<TEXT>
 The partnership created in 1984 to promote a book co-authored by <ORGANIZATION> House </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Republican </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Whip </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Newt </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Gingrich </ORGANIZATION> reported a loss of more than $ 100,000 during its first five years, according to partnership tax returns released today by <PERSON> Gingrich </PERSON>. The COS Limited Partnership was formed by 21 individuals or corporations that each put up $ 5,000 to pay for a promotional campaign for `` Window of Opportunity,'' written by <PERSON> Gingrich </PERSON>, his wife, <PERSON> Marianne </PERSON> <PERSON> Gingrich </PERSON>, and <PERSON> David </PERSON> <PERSON> Drake </PERSON>. One person, <PERSON> Janet </PERSON> <PERSON> Morris </PERSON>, received a $ 5,000 share of the partnership for editorial work. The partnership is the subject of a formal complaint filed with the <ORGANIZATION> House </ORGANIZATION> ethics committee by Rep. <PERSON> Bill </PERSON> <PERSON> Alexander </PERSON>, <LOCATION> D-Ark </LOCATION>., accusing <PERSON> Gingrich </PERSON> of 10 apparent violations of House rules The committee has not indicated whether it will launch a preliminary investigation of <PERSON> Alexander </PERSON>'s complaint. <PERSON> Gingrich </PERSON> initiated the investigation that resulted in the filing of 69 ethics charges against <ORGANIZATION> House </ORGANIZATION> Speaker <PERSON> Jim </PERSON> <PERSON> Wright </PERSON> last week. <PERSON> Gingrich </PERSON> has denied any wrongdong in connection with the book deal. He released several hundred pages of documents today identifying the 21 partners and detailing the organization's finances and incorporation history. The documents, including the partnership's tax returns for 1984-1988, were released in response to questions submitted by news organizations The partnership agreement with the book's publisher provided that the partnership would get half of the publisher's prof