<HEAD>Gas Explosion Kills One, Injures 12</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TURIN, Italy (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 An explosion triggered by a gas leak ripped through the fifth floor of an apartment building this morning, killing one man and injuring 12 other people, officials said. Firefighters said the force of the blast in suburban Collegno hurled debris dozens of yards from the building and damaged nearby parked cars. It destroyed one fifth-story apartment and seriously damaged the floors above and below it, they said. One man was found dead in an elevator, authorities said, and 12 other people were injured, including a man hit by flying debris as he waited at a bus stop.
