<HEAD>Eds: INSERTS 1 graf after 11th graf, ``Expression not ...,'' to ADD
comment from NEA; picks up 12th graf, `Stefan Stux ...'' Note language.</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By RON HARRIST</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>JACKSON, Miss. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The creator of a large photograph of a crucified Christ submerged in urine said Tuesday his critics were flattering the work by creating a furor over it. An organization in <LOCATION> Tupelo </LOCATION> has condemned the federal and private funding of the artist and an exhibit of his work, saying it reflected bigotry against Christians. The creator of `` Piss Christ'' was a winner in The Awards in the Visual Arts funded by <ORGANIZATION> The </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Rockefeller </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Foundation </ORGANIZATION>, the <ORGANIZATION> Equitable </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Foundation </ORGANIZATION> and the <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Endowment </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> for </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> the </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Arts </ORGANIZATION>. The <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Family </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Association </ORGANIZATION> said Monday that tax dollars should not have gone toward the $ 15,000 award for the artist, <PERSON> Andres </PERSON> <PERSON> Serrano </PERSON>. His was one of 10 such awards last year. `` The person at the National Endowment for the Arts responsible for approving federal tax dollars for promotion of the ` work of art' should be fired,'' said the Rev. <PERSON> Donald </PERSON> <PERSON> E. </PERSON> <PERSON> Wildmon </PERSON>, a <ORGANIZATION> United </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Methodist </ORGANIZATION> minister who heads the Tupelo-based association. <PERSON> Wildmon </PERSON> said the <ORGANIZATION> Equitable </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Foundation </ORGANIZATION>, a section of <ORGANIZATION> Equitable </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Life </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Assurance </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Society </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> the </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> United </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> States </ORGANIZATION>, and the <ORGANIZATION> Rockefeller </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Foundation </ORGANIZATION> `` owe Christians a public apology and assurance that they will not be a party to such anti-Christian bigotry in the future.'' <PERSON> Serrano </PERSON> said Tuesday from <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> that he expected some opposition to his work, primarily because of the title. `` I feel when people attack a work of art to such a great extent, they imbue it with a far greater power than when they ignore it and, in that, I'm flattered that they think it deserves such attention.'' As winner of the stipend, the artist selects a work for a national tour. The 38-year-old <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> artist said `` Piss Christ,'' the piece he selected for tour, was a limited edition of four prints. One print, he said, already has been sold to a private collector for $ 3,600. The work is not currently on exhibit. <PERSON> Joseph </PERSON> <PERSON> Slye </PERSON>, a <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Endowment </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> for </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> the </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Arts </ORGANIZATION> spokesman, defended the award. `` Expression not prohibited by federal law is protected by the First Amendment,'' he said. `` Moreover, the endowment is expressly forbidden in its authorizing legislation from interfering with the artistic choices made by its grantees. `` The national Endowment for the Arts supports the right of grantee organizations to select, on artistic criteria, their artist-recipients and present their work, even though sometimes the work may be deemed controversial and offensive to some individuals,'' <PERSON> Slye </PERSON> said. `` We at the endowment do, none the less, deeply regret any offense to any individual.'' <PERSON> Stefan </PERSON> <PERSON> Stux </PERSON>, owner of the Stux gallery in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> which handles <PERSON> Serrano </PERSON>'s works, said the photograph was created by immersing an image of the crucified Christ in a glass container of `` urine he had collected from himself.'' `` When you look at it, you would never know that, all you can see is the image of <PERSON> Jesus </PERSON> <PERSON> Christ </PERSON> in a kind of hazy, yellowish mist, a kind of poetical image. If you did not know the title of it, you could be very enraptured by the beauty of it. It is very pleasing, poetic and spiritual.'' He said the artist uses other body fluids in his art, including blood. `` He was born in the Christian faith, he feels very much a part of that,'' <PERSON> Stux </PERSON> said. `` He has deep religious feelings, but he does not express them exactly the way every other guy does.'' <ORGANIZATION> Rockefeller </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Foundation </ORGANIZATION> president <PERSON> Peter </PERSON> <PERSON> Goldmark </PERSON> said in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION>: `` I respect the right of any individual to object to a work of art, and the parallel right of artists to express themselves and of exhibitors to show works that they deem interesting and meritorious artistically. I think tolerance and mutual respect for such rights may be the qualities we most need in order to get along together on this planet.''
