<HEAD>Atlanta-Area Lending Practices Reported Under Investigation</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ATLANTA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A number of <LOCATION> Atlanta </LOCATION> banks and thrift institutions said Tuesday they would cooperate with a <ORGANIZATION> Justice </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> investigation of possible racial discrimination in the area's mortgage lending industry `` I'm sure the <ORGANIZATION> Justice </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> will find a good level of cooperation among <LOCATION> Atlanta </LOCATION>'s financial institutions,'' said <PERSON> Dallas </PERSON> <PERSON> Lee </PERSON>, a spokesman for Citizens and <ORGANIZATION> Southern </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Bank </ORGANIZATION>. The <ORGANIZATION> Washington </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Post </ORGANIZATION> reported Tuesday that the <ORGANIZATION> Justice </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> wants to see loan records covering the past five years as part of an investigation of the 64 banks and savings and loan associations in the metropolitan <LOCATION> Atlanta </LOCATION> area. The newspaper said the agency's Civil Rights Division, in letters that began arriving Monday, gave the institutions official notice that they are under civil investigation. The letters, signed by Acting Assistant Attorney General <PERSON> James </PERSON> <PERSON> P. </PERSON> <PERSON> Turner </PERSON>, asked the institutions to make the records available voluntarily, it said. <PERSON> Lee </PERSON> and others said the banks have taken significant steps in the past year to do away with discrimination in mortgage lending. `` We are surprised that <LOCATION> Atlanta </LOCATION> was the city the <ORGANIZATION> Justice </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> picked for its investigation, considering all the activities that have taken place in the last year,'' said <PERSON> Bo </PERSON> <PERSON> Spalding </PERSON>, director of communications for <ORGANIZATION> Bank </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> South </ORGANIZ