said entertainers `` have raised your voices so effectively in the cause of so many issues. Can you not raise them once more, in support of a cause so important?'' He turned over to law enforcement officials $ 10 million recovered from drug dealers. He called the money `` the bounty of defeated drug criminals'' and said `` let these funds go to fighting the war they once financed. ... `` And let us send a message, loud and clear to every drug merchant in <LOCATION> America </LOCATION> _ you are going to be out of business.'' <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> said: `` We wo n't build a better <LOCATION> America </LOCATION> until we win the war on drugs.'' He said drug users were living lives without hope or meaning. `` We're looking at a desperation that money alone will never cure. We wo n't win this one with our wallets alone _ we will win it through our collective effort and our collective will.'' In <LOCATION> Los </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Angeles </LOCATION>, <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> met with Republican Hispanic supporters. He said Hispanics were building a better <LOCATION> America </LOCATION> `` through family, church, love of country and belief in the value of hard work.'' He said: `` As <LOCATION> America </LOCATION>'s fastest-growing minority in the 21st century, you, more than ever, will help tell the American story.''
