<TEXT>
 Stock prices posted spotty losses Monday as traders cashed in some of the market's recent gains. The Dow Jones industrial average, up 72.40 points last week, slipped 6.78 to 2,402.68. The dollar drifted higher against most major currencies. Bond prices finished little changed. Weekend showers in one of the driest parts of the Corn Belt triggered a steep sell-off of corn and soybean futures; oats closed lower; wheat futures gained slightly; energy futures plunged; precious metals advanced; and livestock and meat futures were mixed.
