ANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Mining </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> and Australian-based <ORGANIZATION> Renison </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Goldfields </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Ltd. </ORGANIZATION> _ and not buy them back for 10 years. But <PERSON> Mukasey </PERSON> said there was no guarantee the other Minorco-linked entities _ <ORGANIZATION> DeBeers </ORGANIZATION> and <ORGANIZATION> Anglo </ORGANIZATION> American _ would n't buy back the subsidiaries and keep the transactions secret under sympathetic South African laws. He noted at the time that he `` enjoined the takeover because the resulting combination would control 32.3 percent of the non-communist world gold market.'' On Monday, <ORGANIZATION> Minorco </ORGANIZATION>, <ORGANIZATION> Anglo </ORGANIZATION> and <ORGANIZATION> DeBeers </ORGANIZATION> offered to put up a total of $ 300 million bond and pledged not only to sell the previously mentioned properties but to not buy them back for at least 10 years. But <PERSON> Mukasey </PERSON> rejected that offer because, he said, `` members of the <ORGANIZATION> Anglo </ORGANIZATION> group other than <ORGANIZATION> Anglo </ORGANIZATION>, <ORGANIZATION> DeBeers </ORGANIZATION> ... remain free to purchase shares in the three companies.''
