<HEAD>Clothing Retailer To Sell Larger-Sizes Discount Chain</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By MEG REYNOLDS</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>COLUMBUS, Ohio (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Women's clothing retailer <ORGANIZATION> Limited </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> is selling its larger-sizes discount chain <ORGANIZATION> Lerner </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Woman </ORGANIZATION>, freeing up the company to concentrate on its higher priced specialty apparel outlets. <PERSON> Lerner </PERSON> <PERSON> Woman </PERSON>, created in 1986 as an offshoot of <PERSON> Lane </PERSON> <PERSON> Bryant </PERSON>, will be sold for an undisclosed price to a management group led by the division's president, company spokesman <PERSON> Alfred </PERSON> <PERSON> Dietzel </PERSON> said Monday. <PERSON> Dietzel </PERSON> said the selling price, in cash and securities, was expected to approximate the book value of <ORGANIZATION> Lerner </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Woman </ORGANIZATION>'s assets. The deal is expected to be completed in June, the company said. <PERSON> Lerner </PERSON> <PERSON> Woman </PERSON>, which merged with discount chain Sizes Unlimited in 1987, operates under the store names Lerner Woman, Sizes Unlimited, Smart Sizes and Sizes Woman. Aimed mostly at discount shoppers seeking larger sizes, the 382-store chain had sales of $ 223.7 million in 1988. <PERSON> Donald </PERSON> <PERSON> Trott </PERSON>, a retail analyst for <ORGANIZATION> Dean </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Witter </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION>, said Monday the deal meant Limited would continue to provide the <LOCATION> Rochelle </LOCATION>, N.J.-based Lerner Woman with computer and distribution services and management information, for a fee. `` They do n't lose any earnings, and yet through the sale of this they free up some of their assets,'' <PERSON> Trott </PERSON> said. `` It's a fair deal all the way around.'' Columbus-based Limited, with $ 4 billion in sales last year, operates more than 3,400 apparel stores nationwide, including <ORGANIZATION> The </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Limited </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> and </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Limited </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Express </ORGANIZATION>, <ORGANIZATION> Ambercrombie </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; <PERSON> Fitch </PERSON>, <LOCATION> Victoria </LOCATION>'s Secret and <PERSON> Henri </PERSON> <PERSON> Bendel </PERSON> Most of the stores _ with the exception of <LOCATION> Lerner </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Woman </LOCATION> _ are full-price outlets that tend to be located in regional shopping malls, while <ORGANIZATION> Lerner </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Woman </ORGANIZATION> stores generally are located in smaller shopping strips. `` Lerner Woman just had never worked,'' said retail analyst <PERSON> Fred </PERSON> <PERSON> Wintzer </PERSON> of <PERSON> Alex </PERSON>. <ORGANIZATION> Brown </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> ; </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Sons </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> Baltimore </LOCATION>. `` They've got to find a niche, a customer that is n't being serviced by other chains. `` The top management at The Limited just did n't have the time to concentrate on that division,'' <PERSON> Wintzer </PERSON> said. Limited acquired the Sizes Unlimited chain in 1982 and <PERSON> Lane </PERSON> <PERSON> Bryant </PERSON> in 1986, said a woman at Limited headquarters who declined to give her name. Equity of the new corporation initially will be shared equally by <PERSON> Lerner </PERSON> <PERSON> Woman </PERSON>'s management, led by president <PERSON> Raphael </PERSON> <PERSON> Benaroya </PERSON>, The Limited and <ORGANIZATION> Centre </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Capital </ORGANIZATION>, the company said in a statement.
